        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>May 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I beg to acknowledge &amp; thank you for your note of the 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. enclosing your account &amp; informing me that <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>197. 12. is placed to my account at M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Robarts, Curtis &amp; Co.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I am much obliged by your wish to see me at Alford this summer.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. like it much, but I fear other will hardly render it possible.</p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | C. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> J. Higgins. Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Rent collected by Higgins on CD’s farm at Beesby. CD had instructed Higgins to place the rent directly with CD’s bankers (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 3, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-980.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Higgins, 27 May [1846]</ref>). CD’s Account Book (Down House MS) records the deposit of £197 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on 26 May 1847: ‘Draft from M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Higgins (due 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> of June).’</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Higgins resided in Alford, Lincolnshire, close to CD’s farm at Beesby.</note>
        </div>        
            
